    "body": "Thanks for this @Cuteivist :)\r\n\r\nFor case one, we should follow this pattern, where the activity is automatically fetched:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/FkFClTCYKf83RJWoifWgoX/Wallet-v2?type=design&node-id=15096-469417&mode=design&t=R6r2qnmzd7l8JZN5-4\r\nWe show a skeleton loading state instead of the empty activity state and simply load in the activity as and when it is fetched and ready to be shown.\r\n\r\nFor case two, I've added this flow to the designs. Essentially, we can replace the `No activity items for the current filter` message and `Clear all filters` button with the floating `New transactions` button when we know there are relevant transactions that can be shown for the current filter. Clicking that will load in the relevant Tx/s. \r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/FkFClTCYKf83RJWoifWgoX/Wallet-v2?type=design&node-id=19406-190791&mode=design&t=R6r2qnmzd7l8JZN5-4",
